cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a coded computing strategy for distributed FFT. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper applies maximum distance separable (MDS) codes to the algorithm. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper examines the resilience of the distributed FFT to errors during computation. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses communication costs and overhead in the coded FFT algorithm. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new algorithm for distributed FFT.
